emitEphemeralRecord(bytes16,bytes16,byte.notice: Emit the ephemeral event without modifying storage at the given namespace and name. Requires the caller to have access to the namespace or name.

emitEphemeralRecord(bytes32,bytes32[],by.notice: Emit the ephemeral event without modifying storage at the given tableId. This overload exists to conform with the `IStore` interface. Access is checked based on the namespace or name (encoded in the tableId).

grantAccess(bytes16,bytes16,address).notice: Grant access to the resource at the given namespace and name. Requires the caller to own the namespace.

installModule(address,bytes).notice: Install the given module at the given namespace in the World.

registerFunctionSelector(bytes16,bytes16.notice: Register a World function selector for the given namespace, name and system function. TODO: instead of mapping to a resource, the function selector could map direcly to a system function, which would save one sload per call, but add some complexity to upgrading systems. TBD. (see https://github.com/latticexyz/mud/issues/444)

registerHook(bytes16,bytes16,address).notice: Register the given store hook for the table at the given namespace and name. Hooks on table names must implement the IStoreHook interface, and hooks on system names must implement the ISystemHook interface.

registerRootFunctionSelector(bytes16,byt.notice: Register a root World function selector (without namespace / name prefix). Requires the caller to own the root namespace. TODO: instead of mapping to a resource, the function selector could map direcly to a system function, which would save one sload per call, but add some complexity to upgrading systems. TBD. (see https://github.com/latticexyz/mud/issues/444)

registerSchema(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32).notice: Register the given schema for the given table id. This overload exists to conform with the IStore interface. Access is checked based on the namespace or name (encoded in the tableId).

registerStoreHook(bytes32,address).notice: Register a hook for the table at the given tableId. This overload exists to conform with the `IStore` interface. Access is checked based on the namespace or name (encoded in the tableId).

registerSystem(bytes16,bytes16,address,b.notice: Register the given system in the given namespace. If the namespace doesn't exist yet, it is registered. The system is granted access to its namespace, so it can write to any table in the same namespace. If publicAccess is true, no access control check is performed for calling the system.

registerSystemHook(bytes16,bytes16,addre.notice: Register a hook for the system at the given namespace and name

registerTable(bytes16,bytes16,bytes32,by.notice: Register a table with given schema in the given namespace

registerTableHook(bytes16,bytes16,addres.notice: Register a hook for the table at the given namepace and name. Requires the caller to own the namespace.

revokeAccess(bytes16,bytes16,address).notice: Revoke access from the resource at the given namespace and name. Requires the caller to own the namespace.

setMetadata(bytes16,bytes16,string,strin.notice: Register metadata (tableName, fieldNames) for the table at the given namespace and name. Requires the caller to own the namespace.

setMetadata(bytes32,string,string[]).notice: Register metadata (tableName, fieldNames) for the table at the given tableId. This overload exists to conform with the `IStore` interface. Access is checked based on the namespace or name (encoded in the tableId).

documentation.text:
The CoreSystem includes all World functionality that is externalized
 from the World contract to keep the World contract's bytecode as lean as possible.
